This code uses a breadth-first search (BFS) algorithm to find the minimum number of operations required to satisfy the condition. It starts from each cell containing 'o' and explores the neighboring cells. If it finds a sequence of K horizontally or vertically consecutive cells with 'o' written in all cells, it returns the minimum number of operations required. If it cannot find such a sequence, it returns -1.

