This code first initializes the distance to all vertices as infinity, except for vertex 1 which is set to 0. Then it relaxes the edges N-1 times to get the shortest distance from vertex 1 to all other vertices. After that, it checks for negative weight cycles by relaxing the edges one more time. If no negative weight cycle is found, it checks if all vertices are reachable from vertex 1. If all vertices are reachable, it prints the minimum total weight of the edges traversed, otherwise it prints "No".

